label.value: hair plate of prothoracic tibia TiHP3

value.value: Hair plate found on the tibia of the prothoracic leg, near the joint with the femur. It contains three hairs (Kuan et al., 2020).

label.value: mechanosensory neuron of prothoracic tibial hair plate TiHP3

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron with a dendrite in the hair plate of the prothoracic tibia. Its axonal projection enters the VNC through the prothoracic leg nerve (Kuan et al., 2020).

label.value: hair plate of prothoracic coxa CoHP3

value.value: Hair plate located on the coxa of the prothoracic leg, ventrally and near the joint with the thorax. It contains three hairs (Tuthill and Wilson, 2016; Kuan et al., 2020).

label.value: hair plate of prothoracic coxa CoHP4

value.value: Hair plate located on the coxa of the prothoracic leg, dorsally and near the joint with the thorax. It contains four hairs (Tuthill and Wilson, 2016; Kuan et al., 2020).

label.value: hair plate of prothoracic coxa CoHP8

value.value: Hair plate located on the coxa of the prothoracic leg, ventrally and near the joint with the thorax (Tuthill and Wilson, 2016). It contains 8 hairs (Kuan et al., 2020).

definition.value: Tuthill and Wilson (2016) refers to this hair plate as CoHP6 based on the number of hairs it contains, but Kuan et al. (2020) found 8 hairs in this hair plate and therefore refer to it as CoHP8.

label.value: mechanosensory neuron of prothoracic coxal hair plate CoHP3

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron with a dendrite in the hair plate of prothoracic coxa CoHP3. Its axonal projection enters the VNC through the dorsal prothoracic nerve (Kuan et al., 2020).

label.value: mechanosensory neuron of prothoracic coxal hair plate CoHP4

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron with a dendrite in the hair plate of prothoracic coxa CoHP4. Its axonal projection enters the VNC through the prothoracic accessory nerve (Kuan et al., 2020).

label.value: mechanosensory neuron of prothoracic coxal hair plate CoHP8

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron with a dendrite in the hair plate of prothoracic coxa CoHP8. Its axonal projection enters the VNC through the ventral prothoracic nerve (Kuan et al., 2020). It detects leg movements associated with low-viscosity food and is required for the enhancement of the proboscis extension reflex in response to yeast odors in combination with low-viscosity food (Oh et al., 2021).

definition.value: CoHP8 neurons appear to only exist in the prothoracic leg, based on split-GAL4 expression (Oh et al., 2021).

label.value: hair plate of prothoracic trochanter TrHP5

value.value: Hair plate located on the trochanter of the prothoracic leg, dorsally and near the joint with the coxa. It contains five hairs (Tuthill and Wilson, 2016; Kuan et al., 2020).

label.value: hair plate of prothoracic trochanter TrHP6

value.value: Hair plate located on the trochanter of the prothoracic leg, ventrally and near the joint with the coxa. It contains six hairs (Tuthill and Wilson, 2016; Kuan et al., 2020).
